// Varignon's Theorem, Projective Version
//
// Controls:
// Use mouse to move line, which is reciprocal to the mouse position.
// 'd': show dual configuration
// '1' and '2': change initial configuration
// 'f': change line & point drawing style
// 'z': zoom in
// 'v': put line at infinity
//
// Take a quadrangle ABCD and line L. Pick 2 non-opposite
// sides, AB,BC, say, and their opposites, CD,DA: each
// side intersects L & the point of intersection has a
// harmonic conjugate on that side. Draw a line through the 
// conjugates on AB and BC and those on CD and DA, the two
// lines, and a diagonal meet on L at a point.
//
// If L is the line at infinity, the conjugates are the
// midpoints of the sides and we have the original
// Euclidean theorem.
//
// https://plus.google.com/+johncbaez999/posts/hE2bhKZuBzc
// https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Varignon%27s_theorem
//
